Seq66 Arch Linux Package Build
Chris Ahlstrom
2020-07-20 to 2026-05-28

The directory "arch/package" holds a copy of the package build files for Arch
Linux, as retrieved from the Arch User Repository (AUR).

The current version of this package is 0.99.24, the last build before
we switch to the Meson build system.

After all the "Dependences" below are installed, one can descend to
"arch/package" or do a 'git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/seq66.git'.

Once in the same directory as the PKGBUILD file, then run, as a normal
user:

    $ makepkg -si

URLs:

    https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/seq66-git/
    https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/VCS_package_guidelines

Discussions:

    https://www.linuxmusicians.com/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=15133&p=67807#p67807

Dependencies:

libasound.so (alsa-lib-x205ta, alsa-lib-git, alsa-lib-minimal-git,
	lib32-alsa-lib-minimal-git, lib32-alsa-lib-git, alsa-lib-a52pcm, alsa-lib,
	lib32-alsa-lib)

libjack.so (pipewire-jack-dropin, jack2-git, pipewire-jack-git, jack, jack2,
	lib32-jack, lib32-jack2)

liblo.so (liblo-ipv6, liblo)

qt5-base (qt5-base-git, qt5-base-fractional-fix, qt5-base-headless)

alsa-lib (alsa-lib-x205ta, alsa-lib-git, alsa-lib-minimal-git, alsa-lib-a52pcm)
	(make)

git (git-git) (make)

jack (jack-git, jack-stub, jack-dbus, jack2-git, pipewire-jack-git, jack2)
	(make)

liblo (liblo-git, liblo-ipv6) (make)

